<mxfile host="app.diagrams.net" agent="Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/137.0.0.0 Safari/537.36" version="27.1.6" scale="1" border="0"> <diagram name="Page-1" id="hdS8Fb_V-9kqf6li_edK"> <mxGraphModel dx="3848" dy="1143" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="827" pageHeight="1169" math="0" shadow="0"> <root> <mxCell id="0" /> <mxCell id="1" parent="0" /> <UserObject label="" plantUmlData="{
 "data": "@startuml Tower Defense - Use Case Diagram

!theme plain
skinparam usecaseBackgroundColor lightblue
skinparam actorBackgroundColor lightgreen
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

' ===== ACTEURS =====
actor \"Joueur\" as Player
actor \"Joueur Expérimenté\" as ExpertPlayer

' ===== SYSTÈME =====
rectangle \"Tower Defense Game\" {
 
 ' ===== USE CASES PRINCIPAUX =====
 usecase \"Démarrer une Partie\" as UC1
 usecase \"Placer des Tours\" as UC2
 usecase \"Améliorer des Tours\" as UC3
 usecase \"Changer Type de Tour\" as UC4
 usecase \"Gérer l'Économie\" as UC5
 usecase \"Survivre aux Vagues\" as UC6
 usecase \"Mettre en Pause\" as UC7
 usecase \"Consulter Scores\" as UC8
 usecase \"Quitter le Jeu\" as UC9
 
 ' ===== USE CASES SECONDAIRES =====
 usecase \"Sélectionner Niveau\" as UC10
 usecase \"Collecter Pièces\" as UC11
 usecase \"Vérifier Argent\" as UC12
 usecase \"Choisir Stratégie\" as UC13
 usecase \"Optimiser Placement\" as UC14
 usecase \"Gérer Ressources\" as UC15
 
 ' ===== USE CASES AVANCÉS =====
 usecase \"Combiner Effets\" as UC16
 usecase \"Planifier Défense\" as UC17
 usecase \"Maximiser Score\" as UC18
}

' ===== RELATIONS ACTEURS =====
Player --> UC1
Player --> UC2
Player --> UC3
Player --> UC4
Player --> UC5
Player --> UC6
Player --> UC7
Player --> UC8
Player --> UC9

ExpertPlayer --> UC13
ExpertPlayer --> UC14
ExpertPlayer --> UC16
ExpertPlayer --> UC17
ExpertPlayer --> UC18

' ===== GÉNÉRALISATION =====
ExpertPlayer --|> Player

' ===== RELATIONS INCLUDE =====
UC1 ..> UC10 : <<include>>
UC2 ..> UC12 : <<include>>
UC3 ..> UC12 : <<include>>
UC4 ..> UC12 : <<include>>
UC5 ..> UC15 : <<include>>
UC6 ..> UC5 : <<include>>

' ===== RELATIONS EXTEND =====
UC11 ..> UC5 : <<extend>>
UC13 ..> UC2 : <<extend>>
UC14 ..> UC2 : <<extend>>
UC16 ..> UC4 : <<extend>>
UC17 ..> UC6 : <<extend>>
UC18 ..> UC6 : <<extend>>

' ===== NOTES EXPLICATIVES =====
note right of UC2
 Le joueur sélectionne un 
 emplacement libre et choisit
 le type de tour à construire
end note

note right of UC4
 Permet de transformer une tour
 existante en un autre type
 (Fire, Ice, Wind, Basic)
end note

note bottom of UC6
 Le joueur doit défendre contre
 des vagues d'ennemis de plus
 en plus difficiles
end note

note left of UC16
 Les joueurs expérimentés peuvent
 combiner différents types de tours
 pour créer des synergies
end note

@enduml",
 "format": "svg"
}" id="Tb6W-JxO7Xlhz5i32_RY-1"> <mxCell style="shape=image;noLabel=1;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;image=data:image/svg+xml,;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="-1270" y="230" width="2768" height="734" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> </UserObject> </root> </mxGraphModel> </diagram> </mxfile>

g.text: le type de tour à construire
